The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) says eight people tested positive for coronavirus on Saturday. The figure is the country’s lowest single-day count since January 22, 2022 when 29 cases were reported. The latest COVID infections were published in the agency’s update for February 12, 2022. A breakdown of new cases showed that the federal capital territory (FCT) recorded the highest number of fresh infections with four positive samples, followed by Rivers and Kaduna with three and one, respectively. According to the figures published by the NCDC, Lagos, the epicentre of the pandemic, did not record any new case within the past 24 hours. One person was confirmed to have died of COVID-19 complications on Saturday, bringing the death toll to 3,141. Six patients were discharged on Saturday after recovering from the infection, raising the country’s total recovery figure to 230,323. A total of 253,978 coronavirus infections have now been confirmed across the country. 8 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; FCT-4Rivers-3Kaduna-1 253,978 confirmed 230,323 discharged 3,141 deaths #TakeResponsibility pic.twitter.com/HjIz1LS9yi — NCDC (@NCDCgov) February 13, 2022 